Program: The History Hour
Title: The 1948 French Miners' Strike
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p04h15gl
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 27 Nov 2016
This week, the French Miners' strike of 1948, 50 years since the launch of the Cabaret musical, the Silk Letters Movement of British India, the plane-spotters jailed for spying and how to save baby elephants! (Photo: French President Francois Hollande welcomes former striker Norbert Gilmez during a ceremony at the Elysee Palace in Paris. September 2016. Credit:Reuters.) Show less